                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123B641/21.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 6 just received. Consul Bonney and wire were in Mexico City May 5 and
                    Department understands they left next day for Puerto Mexico with a large number
                    of other refugees. Brazilian Minister reports that he is doing everything
                    possible to secure the release of Vice Consul Silliman but owing to the fact
                    that wires have been cut between Mexico City and Saltillo communication
                    difficult.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
